events.name: Golden State Warriors at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Steph Curry scored 34 points and the Golden State Warriors dominated on the offensive glass in a 120-109 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Steph Curry scores 34 points, Warriors dominate offensive glass in 120-109 victory over Pistons

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 23 points, and the Indiana Pacers routed the San Antonio Spurs 152-111 on Monday night for coach Rick Carlisle's 900th career victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton, Pacers get Carlisle his 900th win with 152-111 rout of Spurs
Doncic returns after bumping head, scores 29 as Mavs rally again, beat Magic 117-102

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 29 of his season-high 48 points in the third quarter and the Philadelphia 76ers rolled to their fifth straight victory, 146-128 over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 48 points, 76ers beat Wizards 146-128 for 5th win in a row

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 36 points and 12 rebounds to help the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Brooklyn Nets 129-125 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo has 36 points and 12 rebounds, Bucks beat Nets 129-125

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo took charge. Kyle Lowry took a charge.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo has triple-double, Butler scores 28, Heat hold off LeBron and the Lakers 108-107

events.name: LA Clippers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 27 points, RJ Barrett had 26 in his return to the lineup and the New York Knicks spoiled James Harden’s debut with the Los Angeles Clippers with a 111-97 victory on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Barrett lead Knicks to 111-97 victory in Harden's Clippers debut

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 24 points, DeMar DeRozan had 21 and the Chicago Bulls snapped a three-game losing streak with a 130-113 win over the Utah Jazz on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine, DeMar DeRozan power Bulls past sloppy Jazz 130-113, snapping a 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 17 points, 12 assists and eight rebounds and Jalen Green scored 23 points in the Houston Rockets’ 122-97 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun has 17 points, 12 assists and 8 rebounds to help Rockets beat Kings, 122-97

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored eight of his 38 points in overtime, and the Minnesota Timberwolves sent the Boston Celtics to their first loss of the season with a 114-109 win on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 38, Wolves hand Celtics 1st loss with 114-109 OT victory

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 30 points to help the Oklahoma City Thunder defeat the Atlanta Hawks 126-117 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 30 as Thunder ease past Hawks 126-117

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic notched his 108th triple-double with 35 points, 14 rebounds and 12 assists, and the Denver Nuggets overcame a 20-point, first-half deficit to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 134-116 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's 108th triple-double rallies Nuggets past Pelicans, 134-116.
